# CODEOWNERS — who is required to review changes to which paths.
#
# Syntax:  <path-pattern>   <owner> [<owner>...]
#   - Patterns work like .gitignore globs.
#   - The LAST matching pattern wins (so put general rules first,
#     specific overrides later).
#   - Owners are GitHub usernames (@name) or teams (@org/team).

# Default owner for everything in the repo:
*               @brassHoncho

# Extra-sensitive: the CI/CD and automation config.
# This directory defines how the project is tested and deployed —
# i.e. the safety net itself. Changes here should never slip through
# without an owner's eyes, since weakening these files weakens every
# other protection in the repo.
/.github/       @brassHoncho
